<h2>What Actually Matters in Email Marketing Software</h2>

Most email platform comparisons focus on template libraries and drag-and-drop editors. Those are table stakes. What actually determines whether email marketing works for your business:

<p><strong>Deliverability.</strong> If your emails land in spam, nothing else matters. Platform reputation, shared sending infrastructure, and list health management all affect whether your emails reach inboxes. A 10-point difference in open rate between platforms is the difference between email that earns and email that doesn't.</p>

<p><strong>Automation quality.</strong> Can you set up a welcome sequence once and have it run forever? Can you trigger different sequences based on subscriber behavior? Basic platforms make this harder than it needs to be.</p>

<p><strong>Pricing at scale.</strong> Email platform pricing typically scales with subscriber count. Understanding the cost curve at 1,000, 5,000, and 25,000 subscribers changes which platform makes financial sense long-term.</p>

<p><strong>Integration with your other tools.</strong> Your email platform needs to talk to your CRM, your forms, and your website. Poor integration means manual work that kills the passive income model.</p>

