<h2>1. ConvertKit -- Best Overall</h2>

ConvertKit earns the top spot on deliverability and automation quality. The tag-based subscriber system is more flexible than list-based platforms, automation sequences are easy to build and reliable to run, and the free tier is genuinely useful up to 10,000 subscribers.

For operators running a content site like OperatorStack, ConvertKit's RSS-to-email automation is particularly valuable. Every new article you publish gets emailed to your list automatically. Set it once, never touch it again.

<p><strong>Deliverability:</strong> Consistently top tier. Open rates 10-15 points higher than Mailchimp in my experience.</p>

<p><strong>Automation:</strong> Visual builder, unlimited sequences on paid plans, tag-based triggers.</p>

<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free to 10,000 subscribers, $29/mo for Creator plan with full automation.</p>

<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Operators building lists around content, lead magnets, or service businesses.</p>

