<h2>2. AWeber -- Best for Locking In Pricing Early</h2>

AWeber has been around since 1998 and has one of the most reliable deliverability records in the industry. Their infrastructure is battle-tested, their support is excellent, and their pricing is straightforward.

Where AWeber stands out is their long-term pricing stability. Operators who sign up early and grow their list tend to stay on AWeber because the pricing doesn't spike unpredictably the way newer platforms sometimes do.

The automation builder is less modern than ConvertKit's but fully functional. Templates are plentiful. The free tier is limited to 500 subscribers which is lower than ConvertKit's 10,000 but sufficient for getting started.

<p><strong>Deliverability:</strong> Excellent, one of the most reliable in the industry.</p>

<p><strong>Automation:</strong> Functional, less intuitive than ConvertKit.</p>

<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free to 500 subscribers, $20/mo for up to 500 on paid plan.</p>

<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Operators who value long-term pricing predictability and established infrastructure.</p>

